g.title: myTitle
g.text: ^: Fight 1 of 6 depending on dice roll
Miscellanous items that do not have have special purpose nor sell for gold are not labelled.
There is no bunch of flowers anywhere in the book. Perhaps it was a mistake, or perhaps it meant the golden flower.
The cap with initial skills make many of the items in the book useless.
The proposed path has a guaranteed +1AT, which helps against the Moon Dogs.
On the other hand, you can potentially get robbed of your gold.
Killing ogre for gems is an insurance against getting robbed.
If you got robbed, buy a golden flower at Ms. Pipes, and iron spike, lantern, and throwing knife at the shop.
Otherwise, buy a fire ring at the jewelers, and everything from the shop.
The silver flute from Bay's Ball saves you from a luck roll with the Hag.
If you failed at Bay's Ball, lose the iron spike and the merchant's pass.
If you got robbed and failed Bay's Ball, you will need the gold from the golden flower and the serpent queen.
Alternative routes for getting robbed and/or failing Bay's Ball are marked by thinner bold lines.
Excess gold/item can be used for gaining stamina and luck.
